7 An Act relating to the Oklahoma State University
Medical Authority; making appropriations; stating
8 purposes; providing an effective date; and declaring
an emergency.
9
10
11 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
12 SECTION 1. There is hereby appropriated to the Oklahoma State
13 University Medical Authority, from any monies not otherwise
14 appropriated from the Statewide Recovery Fund (497) of the State
15 Treasury, the sum of Sixteen Million Two Hundred Thousand Dollars
16 ($16,200,000.00) or so much thereof as may be necessary to address
17 gaps in the Human Performance Project. Such funds shall be utilized
18 in a manner consistent with the recommendations adopted by the Joint
19 Committee on Pandemic Relief Funding on April 15, 2026.
20 SECTION 2. There is hereby appropriated to the Oklahoma State
21 University Medical Authority, from any monies not otherwise
22 appropriated from the Statewide Recovery Fund (497) of the State
23 Treasury, the sum of Fourteen Million Dollars ($14,000,000.00) or so
24 much thereof as may be necessary to address gaps in the
ENGR. S. B. NO. 1134 Page 1

1 phar maceutical expansion program. Such funds shall be utilized in a
2 manner consistent with the recommendations adopted by the Joint
3 Committee on Pandemic Relief Funding on April 15, 2026.
4 SECTION 3. This act shall become effective July 1, 2026.
5 SECTION 4. It being immediately necessary for the preservation
6 of the public peace, health or safety, an emergency is hereby
7 declared to exist, by reason whereof this act shall take effect and
8 be in full force from and after its passage and approval.
9 Passed the Senate the 21st day of April, 2026.
